==German==
===Etymology===
When Konrad Adenauer invoked a german army after WW2, it was christened Bundes''wehr'' to emphasize its purely defensive character, but it is also related to [[Wehrmacht]], the army of the Third Reich.
===Proper noun===
'''Bundeswehr''' ''f''
# the national army of Germany
